ZH: 这家公司独占了市场的40%份额。
EN: This company monopolizes 40% of the market share.
ZH: 这家酒店独占了整个岛屿上最美的海滩。
EN: This hotel has exclusive control over the most beautiful beach on the island.
ZH: 他们想要独占这个产品的销售权。
EN: They want to have a monopoly on the sales of this product.
ZH: 这个大学的图书馆独占了全市最大的藏书量。
EN: The library of this university has the exclusive possession of the largest collection in the city.
ZH: 该国政府已经将电力行业独占化了。
EN: The government of that country has already monopolized the electricity industry.
ZH: 她总是喜欢独占朋友的注意力。
EN: She always likes to monopolize her friends' attention.
ZH: 不应该让一个人独占所有权力。
EN: It's not right to let one person hold all the power.
ZH: 主持人试图独占对话时间，不给其他人发言机会。
EN: The host tries to monopolize the conversation time without giving others a chance to speak.
ZH: 这个公司试图独占所有的核心技术专利。
EN: This company is trying to monopolize all the core technological patents.
ZH: 她认为独占父母的爱是理所当然的。
EN: She thinks it's natural to monopolize the love of her parents.
